	
	 <h2>KDE 4 metapackages</h2>

	<p>We are planning create the following metapackages to install KDE 4 easily:</p>

	<h3>kde4-minimal</h3>
	<p>Minimal set of packages to have a KDE 4 desktop running with minimal applications.
	Contains: kde4libs, kdepimlibs, kdebase-runtime, kdebase and kdebase-workspace.
	</p>
	
	<h3>kde4</h3>
	<p>This would be like the kde-desktop task, containing: kde4-minimal, xserver-xorg, most of the kde modules (edu, games, etc), extragears-plasma and some importants applications like amarok, k3b and kaffeine... etc still need to be discussed what applictions exactly are we including.
	</p>


	<h3>kde4-development</h3>
	<p>It will install the "KDE 4 development platform", it contains kde4lins, kdepimlibs, kdebase-runtime and a Suggests on kdebindings when it is finally packaged.

